public static class CharacterState.CharacterStateComparator
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.util.Comparator<CharacterState>

Orders character states by the natural ordering of CharacterState.getStateNumber().

We use an external comparator for CharacterState instead of implementing CharacterStateComparator because we don't want to have to worry (as much) about being incompatible with equals. See Comparable and CharacterState.CharacterStateComparator for information about that.

Note that the state number of a CharacterState is immutable, so this comparator should be safe to use in a SortedSet.
